      • appliesTo

        public boolean appliesTo(java.lang.Class<?> cls)
        Check whether this query can be applied to a given class. A query can only be applied to a class if that class is a super class or the same class as the query's kind. In other words, the query's kind must be assignable from the given glass.
        Parameters:
